	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So the Television that I've been using for my NES needs is dying (flickering/color loss).  I'll be using a smaller CRT for now, but it's definitely not nearly as nice.
<br />
<br />What I'd like to know is are there LCD's (maybe plasma, but they run too big for where I need it) that have 0 ms.  This is critical to me since I play games that take absolutely precise timing in order to play correctly e.g. Battletoads, Punch Out!
<br />
<br />In short, do I need a CRT to get 0ms or are there alternatives?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


